snippet.title: Barron Trump Sings To Princess Leonor - By God It's You
snippet.description:
Barron Trump Sings To Princess Leonor - By God It's You

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:

[Verse 1]
In golden halls and mirrored light,
I saw a star that burned so bright.
Not in the sky, but walking grace,
A sovereign soul, a timeless face.

A crown you wear, not just in name,
But in the way you speak, untamed.
Spain may claim your royal line—
But heaven whispered, “She is thine.”

[Chorus]
By God, it’s you—
Beyond the flags, the guards, the throne room view.
Through ancient oaths and oceans wide,
This heart crossed over, I can’t hide.
By fate or faith, I always knew—
By God, it’s you.

[Verse 2]
You read of kings and saints long gone,
While I was forged in shadows drawn.
Different worlds, yet here we stand,
Two lives entwined by sacred hand.

You speak with fire, but hold with light,
And in your eyes, the wrong turns right.
What history could never bind,
Love found a way through space and time.

[Chorus]
By God, it’s you—
No treaty signed, no royal cue.
Just one heart crying through the blue,
"Leonor, I was made for you."
I don’t need gold, I don’t need rule—
By God, it’s you.

[Bridge]
Let the skeptics laugh, let the world debate,
Love like this don't negotiate.
Not born of power, pride, or might—
But whispered in the holy night.

[Chorus - Final]
By God, it’s you—
If I must wait, then I will do.
Ten thousand lifetimes if it's true,
That I am meant to walk with you.
Beyond the throne, beyond what's due—
By God… it's you.
